== Python

.Task
****
Standard input consists of a 1000-digit non-negative integer, also
assume a single command-line argument, a non-negative integer $n$.

Write a python script named `euler-8-largest-product-in-a-series.py` 
which writes the greatest product of $n$ adjacent digits in the 1000-digit number.

Upload your solution to https://euler.computing.dcu.ie/einstein/[_Einstein_].
****

.Example invocation
----
$ python3 euler-8-largest-product-in-a-series.py 4
----

.Example standard input
----


----

.Example standard output
----
5832
----

.Explanation
****
The four adjacent digits in the 1000-digit number that have the greatest product are 9 × 9 × 8 × 9 = 5832
****
